263","modifiedByFull":"Petrusson, Rikard","remark":"Updated OFF HIRE in Rotterdam for Flag Change to Danish Flag. Vessel sailed out 27th Nov 15.36 for ventilate COTs. Commenced heaving up anchor 29th Nov 12:18 for proceeding inwards to Rdam / Flag change. Completed flag change 1st Dec 2022 22:18 and had consumed 18.8 mt LSMGO. TCE -2839 / -29800 USD PnL (previous OFF Hire was included time for ventilating, but vessel would have done this even if we didn\u0027t do the Flag Change)."},{"modifiedDate":"2022-12-30T10:02:02.393","modifiedByFull":"Petrusson, Rikard","remark":"Please find below from Master explanation to agents regarding the secure lines to shore - which is self explanatory. \n\n \n\nAlso, I have heard cargo ops is resumed. The loss of time is not caused by vessel.\n\n \n\nqte\n\n\nReply All\n\nForward\n\nDuplicate\n\nPrint\n \nPrin\nPlease be advised that ships mooring ropes are kept tight all the time.\n\nVessel mooring pattern is 4\u002B2/4\u002B2 The berth bollard configuration do not allow proper brest lines. Ships headlines along with spring lines are forming relative shallow angle resulting insufficient force to hold ship along the fenders. The same time berth is not parallel to the coastline \u2013 it is forming 90deg angle with coast, thus entire ships underwater length is affected by very strong tidal stream changing direction with the tide, pushing vessel towards and off the berth.\n\nPresently vessel has placed additional rope forward. Just now it is slack water \u2013 low tide and vessel is alongside.\n\nPlease note that there is no emergency, vessel stern has moved 1m away and ships forward has moved aprox 1.5m away from fenders.\n\nPlease find self-explanatory LOP attached, please revert with countersigned for receipt"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-12-30T10:01:27.933","modifiedByFull":"Petrusson, Rikard","remark":"Vessel did COC at Stapleton Anchorage prior going to IMTT Bayonne \u002B KMI CARTERET. Added 1 day demurrage and bunker ROBs/timings. TC